Mark Kuminski | Middlesex County Personal Injury Lawyer






























Call Today!

732.440.3089












Mark V. Kuminski
Partner



A CAREER OF FIGHTING ON BEHALF OF ACCIDENT VICITMS
As a partner at Levinson Axelrod, P.A., Mark is an integral part of our
	 law firm’s representation of accident victims. Mark has been with
	 our law firm for his entire career, and his practice focuses solely on
	 protecting the rights of people who have been injured by the negligent
	 acts of others.
Mark’s specialty within the law firm is the handling of complex civil
	 cases. He is Certified by Supreme Court of New Jersey as a Certified Civil
	 Trial Attorney. His reputation for excellence and dedication among his
	 legal adversaries and the Court makes him ideally suited to handle your case.
When you work with our team, including Mr. Kuminski, you can be sure that
	 opposing counsel have heard of us. Our law firm has a reputation for presenting
	 powerful and compelling cases at trial, traits which are rooted in our
	 legal expertise and our genuine belief in what we are doing. As a result
	 of the tremendous results he has obtained on behalf of his clients, Mark
	 has been named to the New Jersey Super Lawyers list – an honor reserved
	 for the top 5% of the attorneys in any state – for the last 10 years
	 consecutively.
Results in the Courtroom
Over the course of his career, Mark has successfully obtained numerous
	 significant trial verdicts and settlements on behalf of his clients, including
	 multiple verdicts or settlements of one million dollars or more. These
	 include the following cases: $2,250,000.00 in a fall down accident; $2,200,000.00
	 in a construction site accident; $1,750,000.00 in a fall down accident;
	 $1,750,000 in a construction site accident case; $1,500,000.00 in a construction
	 site accident; $1,500,000.00 in a motor vehicle accident; $1,100,000.00
	 in a fall down accident; and $1,000,000.00 in a motor vehicle accident.
Educational History
Mark has lived in New Jersey for most of his lifetime, having grown up
	 in South Brunswick Township and attended school there. He graduated from
	 Trenton State College (now known as the College of New Jersey) in 1987
	 with a Bachelor of Science degree in Criminal Justice. Mark also played
	 varsity intercollegiate football while attending College. Mark graduated
	 from Rutgers University School of Law at Camden in 1990, and was admitted
	 to the bar that same year. After graduation, Mark served as a judicial
	 law clerk for the Honorable Herman L. Breitkopf, Assignment Judge for
	 the Superior Court of New Jersey in Middlesex County. Mark joined the
	 law firm in 1991, and has been here ever since.
Community Involvement
Mark has been involved with the local legal community throughout his legal
	 career, and has served as either an officer or a member of the following
	 organizations:

Past president of the Middlesex County Trial Lawyers Association;
Member of the American Board of Trial Advocates, an exclusive invitation
		 only organization of the top trial lawyers;
Member of the Million Dollar Advocates Forum, an organization of attorneys
		 who have obtained million dollar settlements or verdicts; and
Member of the National Trial Lawyers Top 100 Trial Lawyers.










